#TO TEST THE API ENDPOINTS.

JAVA PROJECT API ENDPOINTS
Customer endpoints--->
URL-http://localhost:8084/
POST- /customer - for creating a new customer.

Example JSON-->

{
    "username":"billGates",
    "password":"bill@123",
    "balance":0.0,
    "serviceRequests": []
    }

DELETE- /customer/delete/{customerId} - for deleting a customer account along with customer history.


GET- /customer/customerDetails - for getting data of all customers.

GET- /customer/id/{customerId}  - for getting data of a specific customer.

PUT- /customer/id/{customerId} -for updating details to customerDetails.json.

example JSON-->
(with new balance to be updated)
{
    "username":"billGates",
    "password":"bill@123",
    "balance":100.0,
    "serviceRequests": []
    }

PUT-/customer/deposit/{customerId}- for
Updating details to deposits.json and customer details.json during deposit.

example JSON-->
(with new deposit in the bank)
{
    "username":"billGates",
    "depositAmount":110.0
    }

PUT-/customer/withdraw/{customerId}-for updating details to withdrawals.json and customer details.json during withdrawal.

example JSON-->
(with new withdrawal from the bank)
{
    "username":"billGates",
    "withdrawalAmount":10.0
    }

POST-/customer/request/loan/{customerId}-to allow the customer to create a loan request.

Example JSON-->
{
    "type":"Loan",
    "amount":1234.0
    }

POST-/customer/request/creditcard/{customerId}-to allow the customer to create a credit card request.

Example JSON-->
{
    "type":"CreditCard",
    "amount":12344.0
    }

Admin Endpoints--->
GET-/admin/customerDetails-to get details of all the customers.

GET-/admin/deposits--to get deposit history of the bank.

GET-/admin/withdrawals--to get withdrawal history of the bank.

PUT-/admin/approve/{customerId}/{requestType}/{requestId}-it approves a loan or credit card request.-WORKS(changes reflect in respective requests.json file and customerdetails.json file)(pass requestType as a string with no quotes)

PUT-/admin/reject/{customerId}/{requestType}/{requestId}-it rejects a loan or a credit card request.-WORKS(changes reflect in respective requests.json file and customerdetails.json file)(pass requestType as a string with no quotes)